    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.17-18_0001b" />
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Lincoln,
                        2-18-'73
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>We have been reading your biography aloud, and I want to tell you how fine we think it is. ("We" means Mr. and Mrs. Young, and Mrs. Elmer <unclear>Holmes</unclear>, who has taken on a part of the job of reading to me. Sometimes the Three read by turns.)
                
                    <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.17-18_0001a"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                
                    <hi rend="double underline">Dear</hi> <hi rend="underline">Lucile</hi>, its<sic>it's</sic> such a bully job, and often we remark on how excellent your anaylses are.</p>
                
                <p>How I do hope someone with real vision has the opportunity to read the <hi rend="caps">MS</hi>!</p>
                
                <p>I wonder if <hi rend="underline">Dr. <unclear>Pedron</unclear></hi> is a member of the <hi rend="underline">Press</hi> board at <unclear>Missouri</unclear>. If so, has he explained my opinion or general
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.17-18_0002a"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                    
                    attitude towards the book? Oh I am so eager for your book to get a fair break! Let me know anything you hear.</p>
                
                <p>This is Sunday. On Tuesday we go to Columbia to meet the sound truck from Hollywood. You have already heard that the United Artists will make
                    
                    <note type="authorial">I borrow Myrtle's eyes for my writing on the book!</note>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.65.17-18_0002b"/> 
                    
                    a record album of my recitations, I'm <unclear>aware</unclear> &#8212; <del/> ?</p>
                
                <p>I'm making progress on the new book. It is to be composed of <unclear>high</unclear> "spots" <del/> of my experiences only. There is no continuous <hi rend="underline">1, 2, 3</hi> narration of events. It will all be <hi rend="underline">rich</hi> I hope.</p>
                
                <p>"All is But a Beginning" is at the 4th printing &#8212; perhaps the 5th by now. Anway it is doing well, and all readers who will seem <hi rend="underline">hailing</hi> over it.</p>
                
                <p><hi rend="underline">Do you hear or</hi> <hi rend="double underline">have</hi> <hi rend="underline">you</hi> heard of the book.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute><hi rend="underline">Endless love</hi> for you &amp; Bower</salute>  <signed>John</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">I <hi rend="double underline">do</hi> want to see you!</note>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
            
                       
